# Step 6: Rollback API & Dashboard UI

**Phase:** 8 -- Build Caching, Log Streaming & Rollback
**Step:** 6 of 8
**Status:** Not Started
**Depends on:** Step 5 (Rollback Mechanism -- `rollbackDeployment()` must be implemented)

---

## Goal

Implement the POST `/api/projects/:id/deployments/:did/rollback` API endpoint and add rollback UI to the dashboard's deployment list page. Users can see which deployment is currently active, click "Rollback to this version" on any past deployment, confirm via a dialog, and watch the rollback proceed.

---

## Background

The rollback mechanism (Step 5) provides the core `rollbackDeployment()` function. This step wraps it in an API endpoint and builds the dashboard UI that calls it. The dashboard spec (`__spec.md__` Section 9) describes:

> **Rollback (`/projects/:id/deployments`):**
> - Deployment history with "Rollback to this version" button per entry
> - Shows which deployment is currently active (production)
> - Rollback confirmation dialog

---

## Part 1: Rollback API Endpoint

### File: `apps/dashboard/src/app/api/projects/[id]/deployments/[deploymentId]/rollback/route.ts`

Replace the TODO stub:

```typescript
import { NextRequest } from "next/server";
import { withAuth, jsonResponse, errorResponse } from "@/lib/api-helpers";
import { getDb } from "@/lib/db";
import { rollbackDeployment } from "@gblockparty/core/deploy/rollback";
import { eq, and } from "drizzle-orm";
import { deployments, projects } from "@gblockparty/shared/db";

export const POST = withAuth(async (_request, _session, context) => {
  const { id: projectId, deploymentId } = await context.params;
  const db = getDb();

  // Validate the deployment exists and belongs to this project
  const deployment = await db.query.deployments.findFirst({
    where: and(
      eq(deployments.id, deploymentId),
      eq(deployments.projectId, projectId),
    ),
  });

  if (!deployment) {
    return errorResponse("Deployment not found", 404);
  }

  // Only allow rollback to production or rollback deployments (not preview)
  if (deployment.type === "preview") {
    return errorResponse("Cannot rollback to a preview deployment", 422);
  }

  // Check if this deployment is already the active production deployment
  const project = await db.query.projects.findFirst({
    where: eq(projects.id, projectId),
  });

  if (project?.productionDeploymentId === deploymentId) {
    return errorResponse("This deployment is already active", 409);
  }

  // Check the target has an image tag
  if (!deployment.dockerImageTag) {
    return errorResponse("Deployment has no Docker image -- cannot rollback", 422);
  }

  try {
    const newDeploymentId = await rollbackDeployment(db, projectId, deploymentId);

    // Fetch the new deployment for the response
    const newDeployment = await db.query.deployments.findFirst({
      where: eq(deployments.id, newDeploymentId),
    });

    return jsonResponse({
      success: true,
      deploymentId: newDeploymentId,
      url: newDeployment?.url,
      message: `Rolled back to deployment ${deploymentId.slice(0, 8)}`,
    });
  } catch (error) {
    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : "Rollback failed";

    if (message.includes("has been pruned")) {
      return errorResponse(message, 422);
    }

    return errorResponse(message, 500);
  }
});
```

### API Response Format

**Success (200):**

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "deploymentId": "new-deployment-uuid",
  "url": "https://myapp.yourdomain.dev",
  "message": "Rolled back to deployment a1b2c3d4"
}
```

**Error Responses:**

| Status | Condition | Response |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| 404 | Deployment not found | `{"error": "Deployment not found"}` |
| 409 | Already the active deployment | `{"error": "This deployment is already active"}` |
| 422 | Preview deployment | `{"error": "Cannot rollback to a preview deployment"}` |
| 422 | No Docker image tag | `{"error": "Deployment has no Docker image -- cannot rollback"}` |
| 422 | Image has been pruned | `{"error": "Docker image ... has been pruned and is no longer available"}` |
| 500 | Rollback failed (health check, container start, etc.) | `{"error": "..."}` |

