## Part 2: Dashboard Rollback UI

### Deployment List Page

**File:** `apps/dashboard/src/app/projects/[id]/deployments/page.tsx` (or similar)

The deployment list should display:

1. A list of recent deployments (up to 20, with pagination).
2. Each deployment row shows:
   - Commit SHA (short, linked to GitHub)
   - Branch name
   - Deployment type badge (`production`, `preview`, `rollback`)
   - Status badge (`ready`, `failed`, `building`, `deploying`, `queued`, `archived`)
   - Timestamp (relative, e.g., "2 hours ago")
   - Build duration
   - **"Active"** badge on the current production deployment
   - **"Rollback to this version"** button (for non-active, non-preview, non-failed deployments with a Docker image tag)

3. Rollback entries show additional context:
   - "Rolled back to {short-sha}" with a link to the source deployment

### Rollback Button Logic

The "Rollback to this version" button should only appear when:

```typescript
function canRollback(deployment: Deployment, activeDeploymentId: string): boolean {
  return (
    deployment.id !== activeDeploymentId &&       // Not already active
    deployment.type !== "preview" &&               // Not a preview
    deployment.dockerImageTag !== null &&           // Has an image
    deployment.status === "ready" ||               // Was previously healthy
    deployment.status === "archived"               // Was previously active
  );
}
```

### Confirmation Dialog

When the user clicks "Rollback to this version":

1. A modal dialog appears with:
   - Title: "Confirm Rollback"
   - Body: "This will deploy commit `{shortSha}` ({branch}) to production. The current deployment will be replaced."
   - Cancel button
   - Confirm button (styled as destructive action)

2. On confirm:
   - Send POST to `/api/projects/${projectId}/deployments/${deploymentId}/rollback`
   - Show loading state on the button/dialog
   - On success: close dialog, refresh deployment list, show success toast
   - On error: show error message in dialog, keep dialog open

### Active Deployment Indicator

The currently active production deployment should be visually distinct:

```tsx
<div className={cn(
  "flex items-center gap-2 p-4 rounded-lg border",
  isActive && "border-green-500 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-950"
)}>
  {isActive && (
    <span className="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full bg-green-100 text-green-800">
      Active
    </span>
  )}
  {/* ... deployment details */}
</div>
```

### Rollback Type Badge

Rollback deployments should have a distinct badge and show the source:

```tsx
{deployment.type === "rollback" && deployment.sourceDeploymentId && (
  <span className="text-sm text-gray-500">
    Rolled back to{" "}
    <Link href={`/projects/${projectId}/deployments/${deployment.sourceDeploymentId}`}>
      {deployment.commitSha?.slice(0, 7)}
    </Link>
  </span>
)}
```

### Loading and Error States

During rollback:

```tsx
function RollbackButton({ deployment, projectId }) {
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  async function handleRollback() {
    setIsLoading(true);
    setError(null);
    try {
      const res = await fetch(
        `/api/projects/${projectId}/deployments/${deployment.id}/rollback`,
        { method: "POST" },
      );
      if (!res.ok) {
        const data = await res.json();
        throw new Error(data.error || "Rollback failed");
      }
      // Success -- refresh data
      mutate(); // SWR invalidation
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Rollback failed");
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  }

  // ... render button and dialog
}
```

