## Verification Checklist

### API
- [ ] POST endpoint calls `rollbackDeployment()` with correct parameters
- [ ] Validates deployment exists and belongs to project
- [ ] Rejects rollback to preview deployments (422)
- [ ] Rejects rollback to already-active deployment (409)
- [ ] Rejects rollback when image has no tag (422)
- [ ] Returns new deployment ID and URL on success
- [ ] Returns appropriate error codes for failure modes
- [ ] Authentication enforced via `withAuth`

### Dashboard UI
- [ ] Deployment list shows all recent deployments with correct metadata
- [ ] Active deployment has a visual indicator ("Active" badge + highlight)
- [ ] "Rollback to this version" button appears on eligible deployments
- [ ] Button hidden for active, preview, and imageless deployments
- [ ] Confirmation dialog appears on button click
- [ ] Dialog shows commit SHA, branch, and clear warning text
- [ ] Loading state shown during rollback
- [ ] Success: dialog closes, list refreshes, toast shown
- [ ] Error: error message displayed in dialog
- [ ] Rollback entries show "Rolled back to {sha}" with link

